latestIgtvVideos.title: Summer Holiday Morning Rountine with @pregnacareofficial
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
AD | One thing I love about the summer holidays is the slower mornings but with a young baby that doesn’t yet mean lay ins!! Felix and Harry certainly keep me busy and it’s important for me to keep my energy levels up🙌🏼
⠀
There’s no magic pill for taking away tiredness but there are little things you can do to help. A healthy filling breakfast is one of them alongside taking a supplement like @pregnacareofficial from @vitabiotics. I have been taking two Pregnacare New Mum tablets 💊 per day since I gave birth to Felix, they contain vitamin B12 and iron which contribute to the reduction of tiredness and fatigue, as well as folic acid and biotin to help support normal energy release.
⠀
How does your summer holiday morning routine look? Is it similar to ours?! ☀️
⠀
#Pregnacare #PregnacareNewMum #vitabiotics

latestIgtvVideos.title: Anxiety & Me | @tuclothing
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
AD | I recently opened up about my experience with post natal anxiety and it sparked such a reaction.  After my last stories in collaboration with @tuclothing I had hundreds of DM’s from mums (and one dad!) feeling the exact same feeling of dread and anxiety when they woke up in the morning and feeling like they weren’t good enough.
⠀
I know first hand how damaging those thoughts and feelings can be especially when it goes under the radar and untreated.
⠀
Thankfully I spoke out, I got help and I now manage my symptoms easily, I feel so much more like my bubbly self and I’m able to enjoy this parenting journey once again ❤️
⠀
I made this IGTV in collaboration with @tuclothing and I hope it helps anyone feeling the same way and gives you the courage to ask for help
⠀
*medication and CBT therapy has helped me but may not be for everyone. Please speak to a professional to find out the best method of treatment for you!
⠀
#TuBaby #TuBabyParter #anxiety #postnatalanxiety #pmdd no

latestIgtvVideos.title: Sky SPACETALK
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
ad | I was well into my teens by the time I had my own phone and I remember it being the coolest thing EVER 📱 I also remember how much safer I felt once I had one, being able to call my friends I was meeting at the park or calling my mum whenever I needed her (usually for a lift home 🤣)
-
I think 6 is a little young for a full on mobile phone but the Sky Mobile SPACETALK watch is perfect for that in between stage. It’s a smart watch, GPS tracker that also allows you to make and receive calls and text. It’s not connected to the internet so no need to worry about online trolling or your little ones spending hours scrolling mindlessly.
-
They are only able to contact the numbers you input via an app on your phone and you will always know where they are during those times they aren’t glued to your side 🥰
-
Do you think this is something your child would like? What age do you think is ok to give kids their own phones??
#skyspacetalk

latestPosts.caption:
Here’s what you’re getting yourselves into by following me… 🤪 

• I’m 37 going on 22

• Expect a lot of relatable, affordable but fun fashion - usually with a splash of colour because dopamine dressing makes me feel good 🌈 

• Soccer mum, fun mum, skateboard mum, stressed mum - warts and all

• A few wild nights out because you only live once - & if you’re on the close friends list you get the goodies 🫣🤣

• As much laughs and positivity as I can squeeze in - apart from when we’re discussing the great British weather because I CANNOT

I honestly don’t take life or myself too seriously, I love a good chat, reading, sunflowers, food, travel, adventure and all the girly things too 💕
I hope you stick around and enjoy viewing my content as much as I love making it! 😊

When those throwbacks come up on your iPhone 😭😍🥰 As if this squishy little baby is going to be starting school in September!!

He’s ready. But I can’t quite believe it!! 
My rainbow/lockdown babe, born into the most crazy world at a time when we needed him most 😭

Honestly how on earth do we slow down time? Do you have a small person starting school this year??

I think it’s very easy to get swept up in what other people are doing on social media when you’re a content creator or aspiring to be one.

But I’ll take dancing to 90s boybands while cleaning the loo over a polished promo any day. So here’s your reminder: you are the content. Your daily chaos, home cooked meals, how you style your hair, the stuff you think is ‘boring’… that’s the gold. 📸

✨ Whats a dull bit of your day that you secretly love watching in other people’s content? ✨
